--- a/Programmer/bin/jtagserver.orig
+++ b/Programmer/bin/jtagserver.patched
@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@
+# WHY: jtagserver (the binary inside gowin-eda-programmer) spawns a subprocess
+# that hard-codes /usr/local/bin/python3 as the Python interpreter path.
+# On Arch Linux, Python 3 lives at /usr/bin/python3; /usr/local/bin/ is empty
+# by default, so jtagserver fails to start the subprocess it needs for USB
+# communication with the GWU2U programmer (CDC-class device, 33aa:0020).
+#
+# FIX: The PKGBUILD creates /usr/local/bin/python3 -> /usr/bin/python3 so the
+# embedded path resolves. Arch policy discourages files under /usr/local, but
+# this is a local-use PKGBUILD specifically to work around this upstream defect.
+# Upstreamable fix would be a patch to the jtagserver binary or a wrapper script
+# that sets PATH before exec'ing jtagserver -- but jtagserver is a closed binary.
+#
+# NOTE: This file is a documentation patch only; the symlink is created in package().
